commit.message:
Error when merging pictures

There was an error when merging pictures. If multiple files where merged the picture dictionary was always overwritten by the last inputtextdoc. Call dictionary method update instead to concat the textdoc and inputtextdoc dictionaries.

commit.message:
Update caches instead of clearing them when calling removeChild()

This prevents cache corruptions when an element is removed and another
one is immediately added to a document. In such a situation, the element
cache of the document only contains the latter element. Since this cache
is not empty any more, further calls to other methods (such as
getElementsByType) do not trigger cache rebuilding, yielding to
incorrect results.

commit.message:
Use defusedxml which protects against a bunch of XML-vulnerabilities.

It protects against:

- billion laughs / exponential entity expansion
- quadratic blowup entity expansion
- external entity expansion (remote)
- external entity expansion (local file)

Add tests for various XML vulnerabilities.

This tests for:
- Billion laughs attack
- Quadratic blowup attack
- External entity attacks on local files
- External entity attack on remote files

Add support for Python 3.7.

Dropping Python 3.3 from the Travis-CI tests as it was already dropped from `tox.ini` and is no longer supported. Additionally it breaks on Travis-CI.
fix odf/opendocument.py toXml needs codecs import
Starting 1.3.7 development
Getting ready for release 1.3.6
Python 3.3.x has reached end-of-life. 2017-09-29
